      "code": "FL 2774",
      "subject": "FL",
      "number": "2774",
      "level": 2000,
      "title": "Multilingualism and Language Contact",
      "credits": {
        "min": 3,
        "max": 3
      },
      "isVariableCredit": false,
      "description": "Exploration of multilingualism as a social and linguistic phenomenon. Examination of language practices in multilingual contexts around the world. Analysis of current socio-political policies pertaining to language in situations of language contact. Discussion of linguistic rights, such as economic opportunities, education, and national languages, and their connection to world affairs. Exploration of language revitalization efforts for endangered languages. Taught in English.",
